``` ::: ::: ## 5. Describe the spatial patterns revealed by the kernel density maps From the density map above, it shows that the crossroads has the highest density among the all other roads. Those are popular pick-up points. This also shows a behaviour of passengers are more likely to take their ride in main streets. This implies that more grab cars will pass by the main streets as well.
